# Network Device Configuration Automation with Ansible Roles and Collections

This project demonstrates how to use Ansible roles and content collections to automate the configuration of SNMP, NETCONF, and syslog across multiple network devices from different vendors, including Juniper, Cisco, and Arista. Additionally, it includes tasks for exploring supported network resource modules using the `network.base` collection.

