---

## Overview

This project automates network configuration tasks, including:
- Enabling NETCONF on Juniper devices.
- Configuring SNMP settings on Juniper, Cisco, and Arista devices.
- Configuring syslog on Cisco devices.
- Listing supported network resource modules for Cisco IOS devices.

The project leverages Ansible roles and collections to streamline playbook design and enhance modularity.

---

## Project Structure

```plaintext
simplify-review/
├── ansible.cfg               # Ansible configuration file with collection paths and repository details
├── collections/
│   └── requirements.yml      # Specifies required collections and their versions
├── tasks/
│   ├── arista_snmp.yml       # SNMP configuration tasks for Arista devices
│   ├── cisco_snmp.yml        # SNMP configuration tasks for Cisco devices
│   ├── juniper_netconf_enable.yml  # NETCONF enablement tasks for Juniper devices
│   ├── juniper_snmp.yml      # SNMP configuration tasks for Juniper devices
├── monitoring.yml            # Main playbook for configuring network monitoring
├── syslog.yml                # Playbook for configuring syslog on managed devices
├── resource_modules.yml      # Playbook for listing supported resource modules
└── verify_monitoring.yml     # Playbook for verifying the configurations

